HEADWORD: Semidetached
<hw>Sem`i*de*tached"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Half
detached; partly distinct or separate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Semidetached house</b></col>, <cd>one of two tenements
under a single roof, but separated by a party wall.</cd>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

